This paper deals with the application of AI systems in making life-critical decisions, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms and image classification, which are subfields of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computer Vision (cs.CV), respectively. Additionally, the paper applies the proposed framework to semi-autonomous driving data, which falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the potential security risks associated with black box AI systems, which is a topic covered under the subfield of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
